# Expense Operating Advertising Press Direct Amount

## identifier
de7561

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of advertising costs paid or payable directly to newspaper organisations, that have been expensed during the relevant period, other than those for sponsorship. Advertising expenses are the costs incurred by a business for promotional and publicity campaigns aimed at bringing the activities of the business to the attention of consumers for the purpose of increasing sales.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Expense.Operating.AdvertisingPressDirect.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpr/bafpr2.02.06
- period=duration
